Former Bafana Bafana coach Shakes Mashaba has lost his court bid to prevent South African Football Association (SAFA) from appointing a new coach.Mashaba s case was taken to arbitration early this month, after both SAFA and mashaba failed to reach consensus.Mashaba was fired as Bafana coach in December after being found guilty of gross misconduct, insubordination and violating SAFA&#8217;s communications policy.The former Bafana coach approached the Labour Court to interdict his former employers from filling the post until the CCMA has finalised his dismissal challenge matter.Mashaba was suspended with immediate effect from his coaching duties after he refused to speak to media personnel, and berating safa president on live television at Peter Mokaba Stadium.Immediately after the Game SAFA issued a statement saying that Mashaba will not be accompanying the team on their trip to Mozambique. Bafana Bafana Head Coach Ephraim Shakes Mashaba will not join the team on their trip to Mozambique as the Association has deemed it necessary to employ disciplinary measures after a regrettable incident at Peter Mokaba Stadium on Saturday, 12 November 2016.Assistant Coach Owen da Gama will take charge of the team in the above-mentioned international friendly match against Mozambique on Tuesday, 15 November 2016 in Maputo,&#8221; SAFA said in a statement.-Sipho Jack